<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-10-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-10-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="341" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                    <head>No. 340.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Daggett</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Honolulu</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-13"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 13, 1883</date>.
                            (Received October 29.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 94.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to inclose herewith a printed copy of
                        the protest<note n="*" xml:id="d341fn1">For inclosure, see inclosure to note
                            from Mr. Carter to Mr. Frelinghuysen, October 18, 1883, <ref target="#pg_575">page 575</ref>.</note> of the Hawaiian Government
                        against the further extinguishment of the nationalities of the Polynesian
                        Islands through the annexation by foreign states. * * *</p>
                    <p>Very respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>ROLLIN M. DAGGETT.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>